extends ../template-cdn-en
include ../mixins-en

block head
  title Bootstrap 4 tutorial: Utilities (1): Borders / Clearfix / Close icon

block body
  div.container
    +pageHeader("utilities-1")
      p.lead Utilities (1): 
        a(href="#borders") Borders
        |  / 
        a(href="#clearfix") Clearfix
        |  / 
        a(href="#close-icon") Close icon

    h2.mt-2#borders
      +extLink("https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.1/utilities/borders/") Borders
    h4.mt-3#borders-border
      +extLink("https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.1/utilities/borders/#border") Border
    - const borders= " -top -right -bottom -left".split(" ")
    - const dirRE = `(${borders.slice(1).join("|")})?`
    h5.mt-3.mb-1#borders-additive Additive
    p.mt-1.mb-2
      code= `.border${dirRE}`
    p.my-2 Specifying a direction draws a border only on the specified side.
    div.row
      each b in borders
        div.col-lg.col-md-4.col-sm-6.mb-3
          code= `.border${b}`
          div(class=`border${b} ` style="width: 8rem; height: 8rem; background: #fdfdfd;")
    h5.mt-3.mb-1#borders-subtractive Subtractive 
    p.mt-1.mb-2
      code= `.border${dirRE}-0`
    p.my-2 Must be used with 
      code .border
      |  . Specifying a direction draws borders without the specified side.
    div.row
      each b in borders
        div.col-lg-3.col-md-4.col-sm-6.mb-3
          code= `.border.border${b}-0`
          div(class=`border border${b}-0 mt-1` style="width: 8rem; height: 8rem; background: #fdfdfd;")
    h4.mt-4#borders-border-color
      +extLink("https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.1/utilities/borders/#border-color") Border color
    - const borderCol = "primary secondary success danger warning info light dark white".split(" ")
    p.mb-1
      code= `.border.border-(${borderCol.join("|")})`
    p.my-2 Must be used with 
      code .border
      |  .
    div.row
      each c in borderCol
        div(class=`col-lg-3 col-md-4 col-sm-6 mb-3 pb-2${c == "white" ? " bg-light" : ""}`)
          code= `.border.border-${c}`
          div(class=`border border-${c} mt-1${c != "light" ? " bg-light" : ""}` style="width: 8rem; height: 8rem;")
    h4.mt-4.mb-1#borders-border-radius
      +extLink("https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.1/utilities/borders/#border-radius") Border-radius
    - const radius = " -top -right -bottom -left -circle -0".split(" ")
    p.my-0
      code= `.rounded(${radius.slice(1).join("|")})?`
    div.row
      each r in radius
        div.col-md-3.col-sm-4.col-6.my-3
          code= `img.rounded${r}`
          br
          img(src="../img/80x80.svg" class=`mt-1 rounded${r}`)

    h2.mt-5#clearfix
      +extLink("https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.1/utilities/clearfix/") Clearfix
    p.mt-3.mb-1 For example, consider two floating elements on each sides inside of a block element.
    ul.struct
      li
        code div
        ul
          li: code img.float-left
          li: code img.float-right
          li
            code p
            |  (content height is lower than floatings on both sides)
    p.my-1 However, it causes a ploblem as follows.
    p.mt-3.mb-1
      code div
      |  only
    div.p-2.border.bg-light
      img.float-left(src="../img/80x80.svg")
      img.float-right(src="../img/80x80.svg")
      span.mx-2 Text content (height is lower than floatings on both sides).
    br
    p.mt-5.mb-1 It is a famous side-effect of CSS 
      code float: (left|right)
      |  . When a browser calcutates inner height of 
      code div
      |  , floating items are not considered. As a result, 
      code div
      |  does not wrap floatings. In this case, using 
      code .clearfix
      |  resolve this problem.
    p.mt-3.my-1
      code div.clearfix
    div.p-2.border.bg-light.clearfix
      img.float-left(src="../img/80x80.svg")
      img.float-right(src="../img/80x80.svg")
      span.mx-2 Text content (height is lower than floatings on both sides).
    div.alert.alert-info.mt-3(role="alert") Clearfix is a historically famous technique (originally a browser-bug polyfill). But flexbox is a better way for modern browsers. See the example below (no clearfix used).
      div.d-flex.justify-content-between.mt-2.p-2.border.bg-light
        img(src="../img/80x80.svg")
        div.w-100.px-2 Text content (height is lower than floatings on both sides).
        img(src="../img/80x80.svg")

    h2.mt-5#close-icon
      +extLink("https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.1/utilities/close-icon/") Close icon
    p.mt-2.mb-1
      span.text-faded Ã—
      |  ( 
      code &amp;times;
      |  ) is used for 
      a(href="components-8.html") Modal
      |  and 
      a(href="components-1.html#alerts") Alert 
      strong Close
      |  icons.
    p.mt-2.mb-1 Example: displays as follows inside 
      code button.close
      |  .
    div.row.mx-0.my-2.p-2.bg-light
      button.close(type="button" aria-label="Close")
        span(aria-hidden="true") &times;
    ul.struct.mt-3
      li
        code button.close
        ul
          li.att Accessibility attribute 
            code aria-label="Close"
          li
            code span
            ul
              li.att Accessibility attribute 
                code aria-hidden="true"
              li.txt Text 
                code= "&times;"

    +breadcrumbLevel1("Utilities(1): Borders/Clearfix/Close icon") 
